      <p>
        We provide expert American Range appliance repair in Los Angeles and nearby luxury service areas for
        freestanding gas ranges, dual-fuel ranges, rangetops, wall ovens, drop-in cooktops, griddles,
        grills, and warming drawers. Our technicians understand that American Range appliances are built
        for chef-inspired performance, which means they require accurate diagnosis, careful service, and
        experience with high-output residential cooking systems.
      </p>

      <p>
        Whether your American Range burners are not igniting, your rangetop is not heating properly, your
        wall oven is cooking unevenly, your cooktop controls are not responding, or your warming drawer is
        no longer performing the way it should, we diagnose and repair the issue with precision. At
        <strong>Luxury Appliance Repair by Zaricci</strong>, we deliver white-glove American Range appliance
        repair for homeowners who expect premium service, careful workmanship, and dependable results.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Why Homeowners Choose Our American Range Appliance Repair Service</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>American Range-focused repair expertise:</strong>
          Our technicians service high-end cooking appliances and understand the performance demands of
          American Range freestanding ranges, dual-fuel ranges, rangetops, wall ovens, cooktops, and
          specialty cooking configurations.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Accurate diagnosis for pro-style cooking equipment:</strong>
          We identify the cause of burner ignition failures, uneven heating, temperature regulation
          problems, rangetop performance issues, oven faults, and electrical or gas-related problems
          before recommending the repair.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Careful service for premium kitchens:</strong>
          We work cleanly, protect surrounding finishes, and service your appliance with the attention
          expected in luxury homes and design-forward kitchens.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Professional communication from start to finish:</strong>
          Our customers want clarity and confidence. We explain the problem, outline the repair, and
          keep the process straightforward.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Trusted repair in Los Angeles luxury communities:</strong>
          We serve homeowners, estate managers, and households that rely on premium cooking appliances
          and expect a higher level of workmanship and care.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="service">
      <h3>American Range Appliances and Problems We Repair</h3>

      <h4>American Range Range Repair</h4>

      <p>
        We repair American Range freestanding gas ranges and dual-fuel ranges when they are no longer
        delivering the power, control, and consistency expected from a pro-style appliance. Our technicians
        diagnose and repair issues affecting burners, ovens, controls, ignition systems, griddles, grills,
        and overall range performance.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>American Range range not heating properly</li>
        <li>Burners not lighting or weak flame performance</li>
        <li>Ignition clicking or failure to ignite</li>
        <li>Oven overheating, underheating, or cooking unevenly</li>
        <li>Control knob, thermostat, or selector problems</li>
        <li>Griddle or grill performance issues</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>American Range Rangetop and Cooktop Repair</h4>

      <p>
        We provide American Range rangetop repair and cooktop repair for burner performance problems,
        ignition issues, simmer control concerns, and uneven flame behavior. If your American Range
        cooking surface is not delivering the output or precision it should, our technicians can diagnose
        the cause and restore proper performance.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Rangetop burners not igniting correctly</li>
        <li>Uneven flame, low flame, or inconsistent burner output</li>
        <li>Igniter issues and burner operation problems</li>
        <li>Cooktop control and temperature regulation issues</li>
        <li>Gas flow and burner performance concerns</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>American Range Wall Oven Repair</h4>

      <p>
        American Range wall ovens are designed for serious home cooking, and oven problems can affect
        both speed and precision. We diagnose heating failures, temperature inconsistencies, convection
        issues, and other performance problems that interfere with proper baking, roasting, and finishing.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>American Range wall oven not reaching temperature</li>
        <li>Uneven baking or roasting performance</li>
        <li>Convection-related heating issues</li>
        <li>Temperature control and thermostat concerns</li>
        <li>Door, hinge, or seal-related problems</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>American Range Griddle, Grill, and Warming Drawer Repair</h4>

      <p>
        We also service American Range specialty cooking components, including built-in griddles, grills,
        and warming drawers. If these features are not performing correctly, our technicians can diagnose
        the issue and repair the components affecting usability, heat control, and day-to-day reliability.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Griddle not heating evenly</li>
        <li>Built-in grill performance issues</li>
        <li>Specialty cooking surface temperature problems</li>
        <li>Warming drawer not heating properly</li>
        <li>Control issues affecting specialty cooking features</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        We also provide <a href="/range-repair/">range repair</a>,
        <a href="/cooktop-repair/">cooktop repair</a>, and
        <a href="/oven-repair/">oven repair</a> for luxury cooking appliances across Los Angeles.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Our American Range Appliance Repair Process</h3>

      <p>
        Our repair process is built around clear communication, careful workmanship, and reliable
        results. We begin with an in-home diagnosis, identify the cause of the problem, and explain
